com.xatkit.core.recognition

Interface IntentRecognitionProvider

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultIntentRecognitionProvider, DialogFlowApi

    public interface IntentRecognitionProvider
    A unified wrapper for concrete intent recognition providers.

    This interface provides utility methods to connect to a given intent recognition provider, register and delete IntentDefinitions, create XatkitSessions, and compute the RecognizedIntent from a given input text.

    • Method Detail

      • registerEntityDefinition

        void registerEntityDefinition(com.xatkit.intent.EntityDefinition entityDefinition)
        Registers the provided entityDefinition in the underlying intent recognition provider.

        Note: unless explicitly stated in subclasses, this method does not train the underlying machine learning engine, so multiple entity registrations does not generate multiple training calls. Once all the EntityDefinitions have been registered in the underlying intent recognition provider use trainMLEngine() to train the ML engine.

        Parameters:
        entityDefinition - the EntityDefinition to delete from the underlying intent recognition provider
        See Also:
        trainMLEngine()

      • trainMLEngine

        void trainMLEngine()
        Trains the underlying intent recognition provider.

        Note: this method returns once the intent recognition provider's training is complete. However, the propagation of the training information may not be complete when this method returns.

      • shutdown

        void shutdown()
        Shuts down the intent recognition provider client and invalidates the remaining sessions.

        Note: calling this method invalidates the intent recognition provider client connection, and thus this class cannot be used to access the intent recognition provider anymore.

      • isShutdown

        boolean isShutdown()
        Returns whether the intent recognition provider client is shutdown.
        Returns:
        true if the intent recognition provider client is shutdown, false otherwise

      • getIntent

        com.xatkit.intent.RecognizedIntent getIntent(String input,
                                             XatkitSession session)
        Returns the RecognizedIntent extracted from te provided input.

        This method uses the provided session to extract contextual intents, such as follow-up or context-based intents.

        Parameters:
        input - the String representing the textual input to process and extract the intent from
        session - the XatkitSession used to access context information
        Returns:
        the RecognizedIntent extracted from the provided input and session
